remove.undetected.proteins

Source: R/remove.undetected.proteins.R
remove.undetected.proteins.Rd

This function allows for the removal of all the proteins that occur below a certain threshold (detected in at least n samples).

remove.undetected.proteins(
  DEprot.object,
  min.n.samples = 3,
  which.data = "normalized"
)

Arguments

DEprot.object

A DEprot object.

min.n.samples

Numeric value indicating the minimum number of sample in which a protein must be detected to be kept. Default: 3.

which.data

String indicating which type of counts should be used to define the proteins to remove. One among: 'raw', 'normalized', 'norm', 'imputed', 'imp'. Default: "normalized".

Value

A DEprot object.

Author

Sebastian Gregoricchio

Examples

dpo <- load.counts(counts = DEprot::unimputed.counts, metadata = DEprot::sample.config, log.base = 2)
#> The counts matrix contained 295 rows with only NA values.
#> The latter have been removed from the matrix.
dpo <- remove.undetected.proteins(DEprot.object = dpo, min.n.samples = 3, which.data = "raw")
